nsidered that.\x{201d} She leaned forward. \x{201c}Have you any idea where your brother is? Do you think he is most likely dead?\x{201d}Tessa sucked in a breath.\x{201c}Mrs. Branwell!\x{201d} Sophie, who had been attending to the hem of a wine-red dress with a brush, looked up and spoke with a reproachful tone that surprised Tessa. It was not the place of servants to correct their employers; the books she\x{2019}d read had made that very clear.But Charlotte only looked rueful. \x{201c}Sophie is my good angel,\x{201d} she said. \x{201c}I tend to be a little too blunt. I thought there might be something you knew, something that wasn\x{2019}t in your letters, that might give us knowledge of his whereabouts.\x{201d}Tessa shook her head. \x{201c}The Dark Sisters told me he was imprisoned in a safe location. I assume he is still there. But I have no idea how to find him.\x{201d}\x{201c}Then you should stay here at the Institute until he can be located.\x{201d}\x{201c}I don\x{2019}t want your charity.\x{201d} Tessa said mulishly. \x{201c}I can find another lodging place.\x{201d}\x{201c}It would not be charity. We are bound by our own laws to help and aid Downworlders. To send you away with nowhere to go would break the Accords, which are important rules we must abide by.\x{201d}\x{201c}And you wouldn\x{2019}t ask for anything in return?\x{201d} Tessa\x{2019}s voice was bitter. \x{201c}You won\x{2019}t ask me to use my\x{2014}my ability? You won\x{2019}t require me to Change?\x{201d}\x{201c}If,\x{201d} Charlotte said, \x{201c}you do not wish to use your power, then no, we will not force you to. Though I do believe you yourself might benefit from learning how it might be controlled and used\x{2014}\x{201d}\x{201c}No!\x{201d} Tessa\x{2019}s cry was so loud that Sophie jumped and dropped her brush. Charlotte glanced over at her and then back at Tessa. She said, \x{201c}As you wish, Miss Gray. There are other ways you could assist us. I\x{2019}m sure there is much that you know