self to pull the library door shut.\x{201c}How unfortunate that the prospect of your gratitude is not a tempting one,\x{201d} Will said.Gabriel stared at him, his hair disarrayed, his green eyes brilliant with rage. He reminded Tessa of someone in that moment, though she could not have said who. \x{201c}What?\x{201d} Gabriel growled.\x{201c}He means,\x{201d} Jem clarified, \x{201c}that he doesn\x{2019}t care for your thanks.\x{201d}Gabriel\x{2019}s cheeks darkened to a dull scarlet. \x{201c}If you weren\x{2019}t underage, Herondale, it would be monomachia for us. Just you and me, to the death. I\x{2019}d chop you into bloody carpet rags\x{2014}\x{201d}\x{201c}Stop it, Gabriel,\x{201d} Jem interrupted, before Will could reply. \x{201c}Goading Will into single combat\x{2014}that\x{2019}s like punishing a dog after you\x{2019}ve tormented it into biting you. You know how he is.\x{201d}\x{201c}Much obliged, James,\x{201d} Will said, without taking his eyes off Gabriel. \x{201c}I appreciate the testament to my character.\x{201d}Jem shrugged. \x{201c}It is the truth.\x{201d}Gabriel shot Jem a dark glare. \x{201c}Stay out of this, Carstairs. This doesn\x{2019}t concern you.\x{201d}Jem moved closer to the door, and to Will, who was standing perfectly still, matching Gabriel\x{2019}s cold stare with one of his own. The hairs on the back of Tessa\x{2019}s neck had begun to prickle. \x{201c}If it concerns Will, it concerns me,\x{201d} Jem said.Gabriel shook his head. \x{201c}You\x{2019}re a decent Shadowhunter, James,\x{201d} he said, \x{201c}and a gentleman. You have your\x{2014}disability, but no one blames you for that. But this\x{2014}\x{201d} He curled his lip, jabbing a finger in Will\x{2019}s direction. \x{201c}This filth will only drag you down. Find someone else to be your parabatai. No one expects Will Herondale to live past nineteen, and no one will be sorry to see him go, either\x{2014}\x{201d}That was too much for Tessa. Without thinking about it she burst out ind